@subsubsection Executing queries (Using JdbcClient - XQuery)

Even though JDBC is designed for SQL, the @value{mjclient} utility
can be used to query an MonetDB/XQuery server interactively.  Because it
is geared towards SQL usage, all queries have to be terminated with a
'@code{;}' at the end of a line.  While @value{mjclient} doesn't
support the rich timing functions of @value{mclient}, it does on the
other hand allow true interactive querying.  For instance the contents
of the @code{test.xq} file can be interactively be queried:

@verbatim
% @value{mjclient} -lxquery -p45789
Connection warning: database specifier not supported on this server (mserver_xquery), protocol version 4
Welcome to the MonetDB interactive JDBC terminal!
Type \q to quit, \h for a list of available commands
auto commit mode: on
monetdb-> 1 + 1;
+-----------------------------------------------+
| xml                                           |
+===============================================+
| 2                                             |
+-----------------------------------------------+
1 row

monetdb-> (1, 42.0, "Hello World", <node attr="value">test</node>);
+-----------------------------------------------+
| xml                                                          |
+===============================================+
| 1                           
| 42.000000                                     |
| "Hello World"                                 |
| <node attr="value">test</node>                |
+-----------------------------------------------+
4 rows

monetdb-> 
@end verbatim
